<br>
 I would like to introduce myself.  I am Lady Yienie, Lady of Instruction (which basically means it is my job, and that of the instruction staff, to look into the new applicants... confirm sponsorship, keep up with the page ceremonies, etc )  <br>
<br>
I wish it were as easy as you make it sound to become a page into the Lords of the Ters'Tai, however we have guidlines that we follow.  I am here to see that these are enforced to the best of my ability.  I would like for you to review our website.  Join in groups with our family members as much as possible.  Currently there are not many in our guild that is your level, other than alt's.  Even though this task may prove difficult to do at times, I ask  for this avenue to be your first step.  Take this time to get to know members of our family.  I currently have an alt... &quot;eyesdry- level 20 shammy&quot; that is within your range.  If you see me on... send me a tell.  I will group with you.  We do not encourage anyone in our family to page people they cant play with, or assist in grouping.  However, if someone is within your range and wants to sponsor you... I see no problem.  <br>
<br>
Hopefully, this has helped.  If you have any questions please send me an email, a tell in game, or leave me a post.<br>
<br>
Hopefully, you will be within our halls in the very near future.<br>
<br>
Lady Yienie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/blottdrinal.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ariya>Ariya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/4/01 7:40:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/flottdrinalfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A petition of membership</span><hr size=1> Greetings Lady Yienie, fellow Council Members, and Lords and Ladies of Ters’Tai, thank you for taking a moment to speak with me. I did not think that becoming a page of the Lords of Ters’Tai would be that simple of a task, nonetheless, it is a goal that I have set for myself. Thus I will heed your advice M’Lady and seek those within the guild whom would be willing to quest with me and prove to them that I am worth of become one of you. Any assistance from any of the guild members in helping me to achieve your praise would be greatly appreciated. <br>
